						<summary><p>#92. a) Tiruvālantuṟai Mahādeva temple; b) on the western part of the <foreign>mukha-maṇḍapa</foreign>, under the Dancing Śiva, engraved on the three parts of the base: lines 1–3, on the upper part; lines 4–6: on the middle part; lines 7–8: on the lower part; c) personally located and read in situ; d) ARE 1926, no. 248; e) lost regnal year of <supplied reason="lost"><foreign>cālai kala</foreign></supplied><foreign>m aṟutta</foreign> Kō<supplied reason="lost">vi</supplied>rājarājakesa<supplied reason="lost">rivarman</supplied>; in 1926, ARE read the 10th regnal year; f) Rājarāja I (<foreign>circa</foreign> 995 A.D.); g) inscription read with G. Vijayavenugopal.</p>

